# GitHub Linguist + Dependabot + Code Scanning hints.
#
# `linguist-vendored` and `linguist-generated` together tell GitHub that the
# files under test/fixtures/ are NOT first-party project code:
#
#   * They do not count toward the repo's language statistics (no fake
#     "JavaScript 70%" because of fixture package.json files).
#   * GitHub Code Scanning (CodeQL) skips them by default.
#   * Dependabot uses Linguist when deciding whether a manifest is
#     project-relevant; vendored/generated paths are deprioritized.
#   * `git diff` collapses them by default, so PR reviews stay focused.
#
# Even though `test/fixtures/` contains plain text/JSON/TOML, we still mark
# them as `binary` to disable GitHub's syntax highlighting and "code" treatment
# of the fixture manifests (axios package.json etc.) so they look exactly like
# the inert metadata they are.

test/fixtures/**            linguist-vendored=true
test/fixtures/**            linguist-generated=true
test/fixtures/**            -diff
test/fixtures/**            -merge

# Exception: keep README.md inside fixtures rendered normally so the warning
# is readable on GitHub.
test/fixtures/README.md     linguist-vendored=true linguist-generated=true diff merge

# Normalize line endings everywhere else.
* text=auto eol=lf
